gates_info.name: Human Design Gates
gates_info.description: The 64 gates of the Human Design system corresponding to I-Ching hexagrams
gates_info.purpose: Gates are activated by planetary positions and create the foundation of Human Design charts
gates_info.structure: Each gate has 6 lines representing different expressions of the gate's energy
gates_info.source: Human Design System by Ra Uru Hu

1.name: The Creative
1.description: The gate of creative self-expression and individual purpose. The power to express one's unique creative force in the world.

2.name: The Receptive
2.description: The gate of the direction of the self. The power to know one's direction in life through receptivity to higher guidance.

3.name: Ordering
3.description: The gate of ordering and innovation. The power to bring order out of chaos through innovative solutions.

4.name: Formulization
4.description: The gate of formulization and mental understanding. The power to understand through logical analysis and mental clarity.

5.name: Waiting
5.description: The gate of fixed rhythms and natural timing. The power to wait for the right timing and maintain natural rhythms.

6.name: Conflict
6.description: The gate of conflict and emotional intimacy. The power to create intimacy through emotional honesty and conflict resolution.
